# Rimvio Story Layer

**Canonical spec:** `docs/RIMVIO_STORY_LAYER.md` · **Code SSOT:** `lib/copy/story-layer.ts` · **UI copy:** `lib/copy/human-ko.ts`

## Stack (do not collapse layers)

| Layer | Audience | Example |
|-------|----------|---------|
| **L0 Brand** | Keynote, App Store | You were here. And it mattered. |
| **L1 User** | UI, toast, onboarding KO | 흔적 남기기 · 발견 · 그때 거기 |
| **L2 Product** | PRD, Cursor tasks | Trace · Recall · Lineage · Visibility |
| **L3 Engineering** | code, migrations | PinEntity · EventCandidate · `@` registry |

Experience layers (`FACT → ACTION`) map through L1–L3 — see doc table.

## Globe / spatial surfaces

- **L0 personal:** You were here. And it mattered.
- **L1:** 흔적 · 맥락 · 순간 · 그때 거기 — not 「핀 박기」「GPS」「AI Layer」 in hero/empty/toast
- **L3:** Globe = renderer; pins = SSOT; default `visibility: private`
- **Modes:** Personal (now) vs external discovery (Phase 2) — never mix on one screen

## Forbidden in user-facing copy

업로드 · 게시 · 포스팅 · Geo Social · Experience Graph · Marketplace · 좋아요 · 별점

Hero/empty: avoid **핀 박기**, **GPS**, **AI** — OK in **Settings > 위치** only.

## When writing UI or features

1. Add strings to `lib/copy/human-ko.ts` (L1), not inline hardcode when reusable
2. PRD / task description: L2 nouns + L3 constraints
3. Cursor prompt for Globe work: start with `buildStoryLayerPromptHeader("globe")` intent — one L1 line + L3 rules
4. Do not rename DB/code symbols to Korean story words

## PR reject

- Marketing poetry in component names or table columns
- 「Social network」「map app」 positioning in onboarding
- Public like counts or review stars on traces
